{"version":3,"term":{"cols":120,"rows":80,"type":"xterm-color"},"timestamp":1775115340,"command":"python3 demo/run-demo.py f1-f2-2","env":{"SHELL":"/nix/store/2hjsch59amjs3nbgh7ahcfzm2bfwl8zi-bash-5.3p9/bin/bash"}}
[0.054, "o", "\u001b[2mStarting MCP server...\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.001, "o", "\u001b[2mServer started. Running scenario: f1-f2-2\r\n\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1;33m════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1;33m  TRON MCP — Fixing a Bug While Inside the Debugger\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[1;33m════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "Common Lisp's debugger lets you modify live code without leaving the call stack.\r\nTron lets an AI agent do exactly that: compile a fix while the debugger is active,\r\nthen invoke CONTINUE to retry the failing call — no restart needed.\r\n\r\n"]
[1.500, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m── Step 1: Initialize MCP\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[36m\u001b[36m→\u001b[0m\u001b[0m {\r\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\r\n  \"method\": \"initialize\",\r\n  \"params\": {\r\n    \"protocolVersion\": \"2024-11-05\",\r\n    \"capabilities\": {},\r\n    \"clientInfo\": {\r\n      \"name\": \"tron-demo\",\r\n      \"version\": \"1.0\"\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n  \"id\": \"(next)\"\r\n}\r\n"]
[1.524, "o", "\u001b[32m← \u001b[0m\u001b[32mServer: cl-tron-mcp v0.1.0  protocol: 2024-11-05\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[5.572, "o", "\u001b[2m  (Swank launched, REPL connected on port 14006)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[1.000, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m── Step 1: Compile f1 — it calls f2 which does not exist yet\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m\u001b[36m→\u001b[0m\u001b[0m {\r\n  \"method\": \"tools/call\",\r\n  \"params\": {\r\n    \"name\": \"repl_compile\",\r\n    \"arguments\": {\r\n      \"code\": \"(defun f1 (a b) (f2 a b))\"\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n"]
[0.045, "o", "\u001b[32m← compiled  \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(warning: F2 is undefined at compile time)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.001, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m── Step 2: Eval (f1 1 2) — triggers UNDEFINED-FUNCTION, enters debugger\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m\u001b[36m→\u001b[0m\u001b[0m {\r\n  \"method\": \"tools/call\",\r\n  \"params\": {\r\n    \"name\": \"repl_eval\",\r\n    \"arguments\": {\r\n      \"code\": \"(f1 1 2)\"\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n"]
[0.034, "o", "\u001b[31m← ⚠  Debugger activated!\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[31m   The function COMMON-LISP-USER::F2 is undefined.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m   [Condition of type UNDEFINED-FUNCTION] NIL)\r\n  RESTARTS\r\n  ((CONTINUE Retry calling F2.) (USE-VALUE Call specified\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.001, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m── Step 3: Inspect available restarts — the debugger offers to retry calling F2\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[36m\u001b[36m→\u001b[0m\u001b[0m {\r\n  \"method\": \"tools/call\",\r\n  \"params\": {\r\n    \"name\": \"debugger_restarts\",\r\n    \"arguments\": {}\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[32m← Available restarts:\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m   \u001b[0m\u001b[1m[0] CONTINUE\u001b[0m\u001b[32m — Retry calling F2.    \u001b[0m\u001b[1;33m← we'll use this after defining F2\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m   [1] USE-VALUE   — Call specified function.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m   [2] RETURN-VALUE — Return specified values.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[2m   ...\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.500, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m── Step 4: Hot-compile f2 into the running image — WHILE STILL IN THE DEBUGGER\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[36m\u001b[36m→\u001b[0m\u001b[0m {\r\n  \"method\": \"tools/call\",\r\n  \"params\": {\r\n    \"name\": \"repl_compile\",\r\n    \"arguments\": {\r\n      \"code\": \"(defun f2 (x y) (+ x y))\"\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.017, "o", "\u001b[32m← F2 compiled and loaded into the live image!\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m   (RESULT (OK (COMPILATION-RESULT NIL T 0.003 NIL NIL)))\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.000, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m── Step 5: Invoke restart [0] CONTINUE — retry the original (f1 1 2) call\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m\u001b[36m→\u001b[0m\u001b[0m {\r\n  \"method\": \"tools/call\",\r\n  \"params\": {\r\n    \"name\": \"repl_invoke_restart\",\r\n    \"arguments\": {\r\n      \"restart_index\": 0\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n"]
[0.014, "o", "\u001b[32m← CONTINUE invoked — F2 called again with args (1 2), f1 returns 3\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m   The original call stack was resumed, not aborted.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.000, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m── Step 6: Confirm: f1 and f2 are both live in the image\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m\u001b[36m→\u001b[0m\u001b[0m {\r\n  \"method\": \"tools/call\",\r\n  \"params\": {\r\n    \"name\": \"repl_eval\",\r\n    \"arguments\": {\r\n      \"code\": \"(f1 1 2)\"\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n"]
[0.021, "o", "\u001b[32m← ✓ (f1 1 2) = 3  — f2 is now defined, f1 works correctly\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.000, "o", "\r\n\u001b[32m✅ Live debugging complete!\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m   f2 was compiled into the running image while the debugger was active.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[32m   The CONTINUE restart retried the failed call — no restart of the Lisp process needed.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.536, "x", "0"]
